-- Poland Plans to Keep PKO, PZU; Denies Report of Possible Sales Next Year
-- Marta Waldoch
-- 2010-07-30T06:39:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/poland-has-no-plans-to-sell-stakes-in-pko-bank-or-insurer-pzu-next-year.html

          
          
             Poland maintains its plan to raise 7
billion zloty ($2.3 billion) from state-asset sales next year
and has no intention to sell stakes in PKO Bank Polski SA and
insurer PZU SA in 2011, Treasury Ministry spokesman Maciej
Wewior told Bloomberg by phone, commenting on the Rzeczpospolita
report today.  
          
          


  


        